Refocus the product on the chore-payout loop and ship second-user fixes.

Demolish the calendar-canvas scope (whiteboards, shopping lists, supermarket
integration) and the family-name lookup. Replace them with: a 6-digit
device-pairing flow for kitchen tablets, a four-step onboarding wizard, a
parent-elevation path on shared family devices, per-parent notification
preferences with timezone-aware quiet hours, and entitlement-gated free-tier
caps with a 402-style upsell payload.

Add a chore-only Schedule endpoint (GET /api/board/schedule) that mixes
materialised chore_instances with projected cadence occurrences. Add
GET /api/billing/quote so the SPA never hardcodes a price. Drop the
24-chore default seed at signup; the wizard inserts a Starter Pack instead.

Wire migrations into a Render Blueprint (render.yaml) so they run on every
redeploy via preDeployCommand, with an opt-in RUN_MIGRATIONS_ON_BOOT
fallback for hosts without pre-deploy hooks. DEPLOY.md updated to document
the new pipeline.

Schema migration 0008_pair_and_prefs.sql drops the canvas tables and adds
device_pairings, notification_prefs, and the families/sessions columns the
new flows depend on. Drizzle's migrator is idempotent so the pre-deploy
hook is safe to run on every redeploy.
